ht line; give examples of functions that are not linear. <i>For example, th=
e function A =3D s<sup>2</sup> giving the area of a square as a function of=
 its side length is not linear because its graph contains the points (1,1),=
 (2,4) and (3,9), which are not on a straight line</i>.</div></li><li class=
=3D"ccss-math-tooltip tooltip-container" aria-describedby=3D"tooltip-alignm=
