ip-alignment-965">Use similar triangles to explain why the slope m is the s=
ame between any two distinct points on a non-vertical line in the coordinat=
e plane; derive the equation y =3D mx for a line through the origin and the=
 equation <i>y</i> =3D <i>mx</i> + <i>b</i> for a line intercepting the ver=
tical axis at <i>b</i>.</div></li><li class=3D"ccss-math-tooltip tooltip-co=
